The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Wednesday, August 8, 2007

 Tagore tribute

 Cultural programme by Bengali Literary Society, St Xaviers College, on the death anniversary of Rabindranath Tagore, at college auditorium, 3pm.

 Pictures

 Memories of India and An Indian from India, photographs by Annu P. Matthew, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2pm to 8pm. 

 Exhibition

 Rainsong Roulette, exhibition of handcrafted and woven clothes at Soumyas Creation, 10.30am to 7pm.

 Health

 World Senior Citizens Day, health awareness organised by B M Birla Heart Research Institute at 1/1 National Library Avenue, 11 am.

 Art watch

 Vietnamese paintings by Do Duy Tuan at By The Way, Taj Bengal, 3pm to 6pm.

 Miniatures by Mahaveer Swami and Ariane Mercier at Gallery Sanskriti, 11am to 8pm.

 Tribute to Ganapati, exhibition at Angan Art Gallery, 4pm to 8pm. 

 Embracing Modernity, by Ramesh Gorjala, at Mon Art Gallerie, 11am to 7pm.

 Aranya, exhibition by a group of painters, at Artists Circle, 2pm to 7pm.

 Enigmatic Space, paintings by Tarun Ghosh, Alok Sardar, Subhabrata Nandi and Rabin Ray, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm.




